svg.text: ESPR Textile Delegated Act — Key Milestones
Confirmed date
Planned / indicative
Forecast (timing TBD)
18 July 2024
ESPR enters into force, replacing the earlier Ecodesign Directive.
Regulation (EU) 2024/1781
Feb–Apr 2024 onward
JRC Preparatory Study on Textiles begins (1st milestone Feb 2024).
Assessing feasibility of ecodesign parameters for apparel
April 2025
Commission adopts 2025–2030 ESPR Working Plan; textiles confirmed as priority.
Alongside tyres (2027), ahead of furniture (2028) and mattresses (2029)
16 October 2025
Revised Waste Framework Directive enters into force.
Mandatory Extended Producer Responsibility (EPR) for textiles and footwear introduced
12 December 2025
JRC textiles preparatory study reaches 3rd milestone.
Ecodesign design options assessed for durability, recyclability, reparability
31 March 2026 (planned)
Publication of JTC 24 DPP standards package.
Data carriers, interoperability, and infrastructure standards (industry-reported plan)
By 19 July 2026
Commission must set up the DPP registry (ESPR Article 13).
Hard legal deadline
2026–2027 (indicative)
Commission tables textile delegated act; adoption follows.
Timing TBD — depends on preparatory study completion, Ecodesign Forum, impact assessment
TBD (after adoption)
Compliance deadline for textile ecodesign + DPP requirements.
Often phased in over 12–24 months, but exact timeline defined in the delegated act
By ~April 2028
EU Member States must have textile EPR schemes operational.
30 months after 16 October 2025 entry into force of revised Waste Framework Directive
Sources: European Commission, ESPR Regulation (EU) 2024/1781, JRC Preparatory Study, revised Waste Framework Directive
